author: News Tribune
title: Dowden places second at state tennis
text:
Dowden places second at state tennis Finishes as runner-up in singles Share 
SPRINGFIELD, Mo. — Ashley Dowden of Helias finished second in the Class 1 individual state singles tennis tournament Saturday, going 1-1 on the day. 
Ashley Dowden defeated a player from Villa Duchesne in the semifinals 7-6, 6-2. She then fell to defending state championship Yurie Heard of Pembroke Hill 6-2, 6-3. She finishes the year with a 31-1 record. 
Abby Dowden and Catherine Conley took fifth in doubles action for the Lady Crusaders. 
Dowden and Conley defeated John Burroughs 7-5, 6-4 before beating MICDS in the fifth-place match 6-4, 4-6, 6-4. 
Dowden and Conley, a sophomore and freshman, respectively, ended with the year 18-1, setting a school record for wins as a doubles team.
